 On this blog Grammar will be taught in an interesting, fun and laid back way. It won&rsquo;t be like reading boring old Grammar books!




 If you haven&rsquo;t already, be sure to read&nbsp;An Intro to Hindi first. It would also be useful reading over the Vowels and&nbsp;Consonants sections too, this will help with your pronunciation!


 Lessons on this page are grouped into 5 main section; Nouns and Pronouns, Adjectives, Verbs, Postpositions and Videos. Obviously there&rsquo;s some overlap so don&rsquo;t worry too much. Please feel free to &lsquo;mix and match&rsquo; lessons to give some variety; so why not look at one or two lessons from Verbs then one from Adjectives and so on!


 This page is quite long so please scroll right down to the bottom to make sure you don&rsquo;t miss anything! Once you&rsquo;ve covered everything here then head over to the Intermediate Grammar page for more advance lessons!


  


 Nouns and Pronouns


Pronouns&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&#2361;&#2379;&#2344;&#2366; honaa - To Be&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Introduction to Nouns


Plurals&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Possessive Pronouns&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Possessive Pronouns Part 2


Possessive Pronouns Part 3: &#2325;&#2366; kaa&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Part 4: &#2309;&#2346;&#2344;&#2366; apnaa


&#2325;&#2369;&#2331; kuch - Something and &#2325;&#2379;&#2312; koee - Someone


&#2361;&#2368; hee - Only; Part 1&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&#2361;&#2368; hee - Only; Part 2


  


 Adjectives


Adjectives&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;The Negative Case&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;Colours - &#2352;&#2306;&#2327;  rang


Practice with Adjectives!&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Comparing Adjectives


&#2349;&#2368; bhee - Too, Also


  


 Verbs


An Introduction To Verbs&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;Part 2; The Present Tense


Part 3; The Present Continuous Tense&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Part 4: The Future Tense


Future Form of &#2361;&#2379;&#2344;&#2366; honaa- To Be&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Vocabulary Builder: Verbs&nbsp;


&#2360;&#2325;&#2344;&#2366; saknaa - &lsquo;Can&rsquo;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;Past Tense Part 1; Was and Were


&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;Past Tense Part 2; Past Continuous Tense


Imperatives Part 1: &#2310;&#2346; aap&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Imperatives Part 2: &#2340;&#2369;&#2350; tum


Imperatives Part 3: &#2340;&#2370; too&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;Imperatives Part 4: Negatives


The Future Conditional Tense&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&#2330;&#2366;&#2361;&#2344;&#2366; caahnaa - To Want


The Past Imperfect Tense&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; The Future Continuous Tense


  


