          </ul></div><div id="posts"><article class="post type-text" id=""><aside class="metadata "></aside><h2><a href="beginner">Beginner&rsquo;s Grammar Lessons</a></h2><div class="caption clearfix rte"><p>In these lesson we&rsquo;re going to look at Basic Grammar rules in Hindi. This is perfect if you want to expand your knowledge and be able to make your own Hindi sentences. If you simply want to learn Conversational Phrases then head over to the &nbsp;<a href="convo">Conversational Hindi Section</a>.</p><p class="center"><img src="http://78.media.tumblr.com/tumblr_ll1ouqru2y1qzfx8l.png"></p><blockquote><p>On this blog Grammar will be taught in an interesting, fun and laid back way. It won&rsquo;t be like reading boring old Grammar books!</p></blockquote><p>If you haven&rsquo;t already, be sure to read&nbsp;<a href="intro">An Intro to Hindi</a> first. It would also be useful reading over the <a href="vowels">Vowels</a> and&nbsp;<a href="consonants">Consonants</a> sections too, this will help with your pronunciation!</p><p>Lessons on this page are grouped into 5 main section; <strong>Nouns and Pronouns</strong>, <strong>Adjectives</strong>, <strong>Verbs</strong>, <strong>Postpositions</strong> and <strong>Videos</strong>. Obviously there&rsquo;s some overlap so don&rsquo;t worry too much. Please feel free to &lsquo;mix and match&rsquo; lessons to give some variety; so why not look at one or two lessons from Verbs then one from Adjectives and so on!</p><p>This page is quite long so please scroll right down to the bottom to make sure you don&rsquo;t miss anything! Once you&rsquo;ve covered everything here then head over to the <a href="intermediate">Intermediate Grammar</a> page for more advance lessons!</p><p><br><br></p><h2>Nouns and Pronouns</h2><h3><a href="post/853847321/lesson-15-pronouns">Pronouns</a>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<a href="post/899032290/lesson-22-to-be">&#2361;&#2379;&#2344;&#2366; <em>honaa</em> - To Be</a>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<a href="post/1031675635/lesson-38-nouns-part-1-introduction">Introduction to Nouns</a></h3><h3><a href="post/1042765159/lesson-39-nouns-part-2-the-plural-case">Plurals</a>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<a href="post/1014098733/lesson-37-possessive-pronouns">Possessive Pronouns</a>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<a href="post/1047461709/lesson-40-possessive-pronouns-part-2">Possessive Pronouns Part 2</a></h3><h3><a href="post/1156594856/lesson-51-possessive-pronouns-part-3-kaa">Possessive Pronouns Part 3: &#2325;&#2366; </a><em><a href="post/1156594856/lesson-51-possessive-pronouns-part-3-kaa">kaa</a>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</em><a href="post/1162464592/lesson-52-possessive-pronouns-part-4-apnaa">Part 4: &#2309;&#2346;&#2344;&#2366; <em>apnaa</em></a></h3><h3><a href="post/4664013205/lesson-104-kuch-something-and-koee">&#2325;&#2369;&#2331; <em>kuch</em> - Something and &#2325;&#2379;&#2312; <em>koee</em> - Someone</a></h3><h3><a href="post/25803859206/lesson-131-hee-only">&#2361;&#2368; <em>hee</em> - Only; Part 1</a>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="post/26588748266/lesson-132-hee-only-part-2">&#2361;&#2368; <em>hee</em> - Only; Part 2</a></h3><p><br><br></p><h2>Adjectives</h2><h3><a href="post/1076764983/lesson-44-adjectives">Adjectives</a>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="post/1093469716/lesson-46-the-negative-case">The Negative Case</a>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="post/1098745517/lesson-47-colours-rang">Colours - &#2352;&#2306;&#2327; <em> rang</em></a></h3><h3><a href="post/1438973740/lesson-67-practice-with-adjectives">Practice with Adjectives!</a>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<a href="post/1600166704/lesson-73-comparing-adjectives">Comparing Adjectives</a></h3><h3><a href="post/6324812777/lesson-115-bhee-too-also">&#2349;&#2368; <em>bhee</em> - Too, Also</a></h3><p><em><br></em></p><h2>Verbs</h2><h3><a href="post/918920151/lesson-25-verbs-part-1">An Introduction To Verbs</a>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="post/938215810/lesson-28-verbs-part-2-the-present-tense">Part 2; The Present Tense</a></h3><h3><a href="post/1004288841/lesson-35-verbs-part-3-the-present-continuous-tense">Part 3; The Present Continuous Tense</a>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<a href="post/1184881027/lesson-53-verbs-part-4-the-future-tense">Part 4: The Future Tense</a></h3><h3><a href="post/1205758422/lesson-55-the-future-form-of-to-be">Future Form of &#2361;&#2379;&#2344;&#2366; <em>honaa</em>- To Be</a>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<a href="post/1210783558/lesson-56-vocabulary-builder-verbs">Vocabulary Builder: Verbs</a>&nbsp;</h3><h3><a href="post/1383686256/lesson-64-saknaa-to-be-able-to-can">&#2360;&#2325;&#2344;&#2366; <em>saknaa</em> - &lsquo;Can&rsquo;</a>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="post/1518014000/lesson-69-past-tense-part-1-was-and-were">Past Tense Part 1; Was and Were</a></h3><h3>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="post/1546814687/lesson-70-past-tense-part-2-the-past-continuous">Past Tense Part 2; Past Continuous Tense</a></h3><h3><a href="post/1695175480/lesson-75-verbs-part-4-imperatives-part-1">Imperatives Part 1: &#2310;&#2346; <em>aap</em></a>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<a href="post/2111368263/lesson-77-verbs-part-6-the-tum-imperative">Imperatives Part 2: &#2340;&#2369;&#2350; <em>tum</em></a></h3><h3><a href="post/2337937750/lesson-80-imperatives-part-3-too">Imperatives Part 3: &#2340;&#2370; <em>too</em></a>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="post/5641710580/lesson-111-imperatives-part-4-negatives-dont">Imperatives Part 4: Negatives</a></h3><h3><a href="post/4316008690/lesson-103-the-future-conditional-tense">The Future Conditional Tense</a>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<a href="post/23877540202/lesson-128-caahnaa-to-want">&#2330;&#2366;&#2361;&#2344;&#2366; <em>caahnaa</em> - To Want</a></h3><h3><a href="post/4903725694/lesson-105-the-past-imperfect-tense">The Past Imperfect Tense</a>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; <a href="post/24771291820/lesson-129-the-future-continuous-tense">The Future Continuous Tense</a></h3><p><br><br></p><h2>Postpositions</h2><h3><a href="post/1116750602/lesson-48-nouns-part-3-the-oblique-case">Nouns In The Oblique Case</a>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<a href="post/1307711856/lesson-61-pronouns-part-2-the-oblique-case">Pronouns Part 2; The Oblique Case</a></h3><h3><a href="post/1133921729/lesson-50-postpositions">Postpositions</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <a href="post/3661541490/lesson-96-compound-postpositions">Compound Postpositions</a>&nbsp;</h3><h3><a href="post/5187717906/lesson-107-more-on-compound-postpositions">Compound Postpositions Part 2</a></h3><h3><a href="post/7310166652/lesson-122-more-about-ko-to">More about &#2325;&#2379; <em>ko</em> - 'to&rsquo;</a></h3><p><br><br></p><h2>Videos + Stories</h2><h3><a href="post/1416574303/lesson-66-the-elephants-friendship">The Elephant&rsquo;s Friendship</a>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<a href="post/1564407772/lesson-71-revisiting-the-elephants-friendship">Revisiting The Elephant&rsquo;s Friendship</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;</h3><h3><a href="post/3383602672/lesson-93-popeye-in-hindi">Popeye in Hindi!</a>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="post/3899887417/lesson-99-aati-kya-khandala">&#2310;&#2340;&#2368; &#2325;&#2381;&#2351;&#2366; &#2326;&#2306;&#2337;&#2366;&#2354;&#2366; Aati Kya Khandala</a></h3><h3><a href="post/5937184650/lesson-112-the-loyal-mongoose">The Loyal Mongoose</a>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; <a href="post/7154893705/lesson-121-indian-mcdonalds-advert">Indian McDonald&rsquo;s Advert</a></h3><h3><a href="post/10687591128/lesson-124-tujh-men-rab-dikhta-hai">Tujh Men Rab Dikhta Hai</a>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <a href="post/17096412668/lesson-127-the-thirsty-crow">&#2346;&#2381;&#2351;&#2366;&#2360;&#2366; &#2325;&#2380;&#2310; The Thirsty Crow</a></h3><p><br><br></p><h2>Other</h2><h3><a href="post/1651654356/lesson-74-the-sad-banana">The Sad Banana</a>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<a href="post/1488246634/lesson-68-tense-review-and-happy-diwali">Tense Review and Happy Diwali!</a></h3><h3><a href="post/3959223301/lesson-100-recap-and-thank-yous">Recap and Thank You&rsquo;s!</a>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</h3><p><br><br></p><p>Have you covered everything here?&nbsp;&nbsp;Is it too easy? Head over the <a href="intermediate">Intermediate Grammar</a> page for more advance lessons!</p><p>Why are you reading this all the way down here? Go and click on a Lesson above and start learning! If you don&rsquo;t know what Lesson to choose then&nbsp;<a href="http://www.learning-hindi.com/random">click here to go to a Random Lesson</a>!</p></div></article>                              
